key "Dah06"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection

\color black
Elimination of stop-words
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\color black
This phase is of some importance since it constitutes a factor of great
 influence in the accuracy of the search.
 The failure to remove stop words inevitably cause noise.
 The elimination of stop words which are words of everyday language and
 do not contain much semantic information must be both in indexing as querying
 (removing stop-words from the query).
 
